d Building construction works which comes under Municipal Corporation. Independently manage the; responsibilities Reviewed Civil work for deficiencies and deviations from the plans, building codes, by-laws or general good; construction practice. Did Quality Control check and testing of construction materials and was fully aware of what the quality; procedures are for all aspects of the work. Verification of quantities in Contractor’s Running Account Bills. Supervised the; Contractors, Engineers and technicians. Reviewed and approved designs, cost estimates and calculations under the guidance of; Sub –Divisional Engineer. Also prepared plans and new estimates along with for special repairs, additions and alterations. Prepared; BOQs’, Estimates and Drawings for construction works.; Worked as Civil Support Project Engineer with TEC International Co. Ltd at JICA Assisted Amritsar Sewerage Project (ID-; P186), Amritsar. Total cost of project was Rs 360 crore where I discharged all the functions and duties as assigned by Team; Leader, India Operation of TEC. Report to client any delays and/or disruptions and requests for extensions of time by any; contractor. Prepare periodic reports in an agreed format at weekly intervals to validate the construction progress reports by the; developer’s contractors, and reports the progress on client contracted construction works. Assist client in performing an overall; evaluation of the Project. Conduct regular Site visit with available Client and Contractor representative to check the quality of; workmanship at site and highlight any non-compliances. Undertook sewer designing, conducted field surveys, survey of; topography, road and highway system, water supply system and population survey to provide data for the project. Support in; delivering the project as per agreed timeline and quality within budget.; Supplying and Laying of UPVC Pipes, construction of Sewage Treatment Plant of 0.223MLD capacity. Conducted; periodic and post-project reviews to ensure project is on track. Conducted field surveys to provide data for the; Project. Monitored the provision of materials. Coordinate and supervise daily activities of pipe laying crews.; PROFESSIONAL; STRENGTHS: -; Core strength in working; team-based environment.; and withstand site; conditions.; Good verbal and written; 3rd Prize in Quiz Competition Organized by CESA (02/2012); Co-chaired Geo-live 2021; International Webinar on Geotechnical Engineering; Organized by School of Civil Engineering, Lovely Professional University; Autodesk Civil 3D 2022 Essential Training (04/2023); LinkedIn LEARNING; Auto CAD 2019 Essential Training (04/2023); Microsoft Project Essential Training (04/2023); Excel Essential Training (Microsoft 365)- (04/2023); Construction Project Management Specialization Course (05/2021 – 07/2021); COURSERA; Construction Project Management (05/2021 – 06/2021); Construction Scheduling (06/2021 – 07/2021); Construction Cost Estimating and Cost Control (06/2021 – 07/2021); Construction Finance (06/2021 – 07/2021); Construction Industry- The Way Forward (06/2021 – 07/2021); INDUSTRIAL TRAINING (01/2014 - 04/2014); MOTIA DEVELPORS PVT. LTD; STAAD Pro (07/2013); CADD CENTRE; Introduction to CAD (04/2013); Auto CAD (Civil) (12/2011 - 01/2012); VISUAL MEDIA; 3Ds MAX (12/2011 - 01/2012)"}]'::jsonb, 'F:\Resume All 1\Resume PDF\Hardeep Singh Jassal.pdf', 'Name: Work Experience

